                            <td>Ew got ku ew hat√Æ ye.</td>
                        </tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>

                <div class="example-box">
                    <div class="example-title">üìå Tense Examples:</div>
                    
                    <div class="example-item">
                        <div class="kurdish-text"><strong>Direct:</strong> Ew got: "Ez her roj dixw√Ænim."</div>
                        <div class="english-text">He said: "I read every day."</div>
                        <div class="kurdish-text" style="margin-top: 10px;"><strong>Indirect:</strong> Ew got ku ew her roj dixw√Æne.</div>
                        <div class="english-text">He said that he reads every day.</div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="example-item">
                        <div class="kurdish-text"><strong>Direct:</strong> Min got: "Ez duh √ß√ªm bajar√™."</div>
                        <div class="english-text">I said: "I went to the city yesterday."</div>
                        <div class="kurdish-text" style="margin-top: 10px;"><strong>Indirect:</strong> Min got ku ez duh √ß√ªme bajar√™.</div>
                        <div class="english-text">I said that I went to the city yesterday.</div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="example-item">
                        <div class="kurdish-text"><strong>Direct:</strong> Ew got: "Ez √™ sibe herim dibistan√™."</div>
                        <div class="english-text">He said: "I will go to school tomorrow."</div>
                        <div class="kurdish-text" style="margin-top: 10px;"><strong>Indirect:</strong> Ew got ku ew √™ sibe here dibistan√™.</div>
                        <div class="english-text">He said that he would go to school tomorrow.</div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="note-box">
                    <div class="note-title">üí° Tense Note!</div>
                    <p style="line-height: 1.8;">
                        Unlike English, Kurdish often <strong>keeps the original tense</strong> in indirect speech, especially:<br>
                        ‚Ä¢ When the statement is still true<br>
                        ‚Ä¢ When reporting recent speech<br>
                        ‚Ä¢ In informal contexts<br><br>
                        However, tense may shift when the context requires it.
                    </p>
